	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-08-25T09:33:43">Servelec Group plc is engaged in providing software, hardware and services to the United Kingdom health and social care, oil and gas, power and nuclear, water, utilities and broadcast sectors. The Company operates in two segments: Servelec Health and Social Care, and Servelec Automation. Its Servelec Health and Social Care specializes in the design, development and implementation of electronic patient record (EPR) and patient administration software (PAS) and social care case management software within secondary care and social care settings. Its Servelec Automation provides control systems to blue-chip companies in the United Kingdom, focusing on the oil and gas, nuclear, power, water, utilities and broadcast industries. Its Servelec Automation segment operates as two segments: Servelec Controls and Servelec Technologies.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-08-27T23:52:51">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Servelec Group PLC revenues increased 20% to L30M. Net income increased 9% to L3.7M. Revenues reflect Servelec Healthcare segment increase from L7.4M to L15.6M. Net income was partially offset by Central segment loss increase of 46% to L2.9M, Servelec Automation segment income decrease of 4% to L3M. Dividend per share remained flat at L0.02.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
